LAGOS – Lagos State Government has re-emphasized its resolve to enforce the ban on commercial motorcycles, popularly known as Okada in six local governments in the state come June 1, 2022. The state government re-emphasized its position in a tweet on the state’s official twitter handle, @followlasg, accompanied by a video showing the number of Okada accidents in the state. “Lagos State Government will no longer tolerate the menace of commercial motorcycles. From June 1st, Lagos State Government has totally ban them in six Local Governments.” -Advertisement- See tweet below;